Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Daniel Kim

2023-03-12

My meme

The papers I take always damage my brain and so I wanted to share how I feel using my meme of choice

library(magick)

elmo <- image_read("1.png") #first image initialization
elmo %>%
  image_scale(550) #scale test

utake <- image_read("2.jpg")# second image initialization
utake %>%
  image_resize("200x200!")#resizing test

elmo <- image_read("1.png") %>%
  image_scale(500)%>%
  image_annotate("Me", location = "+220+200", size = 25, color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate("uni classes", location = "+300+175", size = 25, color = "#000000")
elmo #first annotated image

utake <- image_read("2.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_annotate("Me taking data science cause I like stats", location = "+10+200", size = 20, color = "#F4EDD3") %>%
  image_annotate("CS papers", location = "+240+260", size = 20, color = "#F4EDD3")
utake #second annotated image

image_append(c(elmo, utake)) #meme submission

final_meme <- image_append(c(elmo, utake)) %>%
  image_write("my_meme.png") #.png conversion

My animated GIF

These are just some of the images that live rent free in my head and make me chuckle.

library(magick)

frame1 <- image_read("ani1.png") #setting up images
frame2 <- image_read("ani2.jpg") #setting up images
frame3 <- image_read("ani3.jpg") #setting up images
frame4 <- image_read("ani4.jpeg") #setting up images

animation <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4) #concatenating images together

animation %>% 
  image_animate(fps = 1) %>% 
  image_write("my_animation.gif")
animation
